This paper is about a deep learning architecture for spoken language understanding, which is a subfield of natural language processing. The paper specifically focuses on the semantic decoder component of a Statistical Spoken Dialogue System. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is the primary category for natural language processing research. The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The paper also involves training neural networks, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with dialogue systems, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Dialogue) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
